I’ve ruled out several “instant admin change” reports as governance/design risks rather than vulnerabilities. One remaining low-confidence area is cross-market reentrancy, which depends entirely on whether any concrete `doTransferOut` path can invoke attacker code before the source market updates storage, so I’m checking the actual token/ETH transfer implementations now.
