wer guarded by `msg.sender == admin` plus interface checks. This is governance trust, not a protocol bug."},{"title":"Comptroller Can Be Changed on CTokens","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`_setComptroller` is an explicit admin hook and verifies the new target implements the comptroller marker. The candidate is a generic privileged-upgrade concern, not a vulnerability."},{"title":"Borrow Cap Guardian Can Disable Borrowing","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The claim is factually incorrect for this code: `_setMarketBorrowCaps` documents and implements `0` as unlimited borrowing, not disabled borrowing. More generally, borrow-cap setting is an intended privileged control."},{"title":"COMP Accrual Fix Function Allows Arbitrary Adjustment","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The function is a one-off admin-only remediation hook and the candidate relies on trusted-admin abuse. The reportable issue in this area is instead that recorded `compReceivable` debt is never enforced."},{"title":"Unitroller Delegatecall Reentrancy Risk","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is the standard upgradeable proxy delegation pattern. The candidate does not show a distinct exploit beyond compromising the trusted implementation/admin path."},{"title":"Market Deprecation Can Be Abused for Immediate Liquidation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`isDeprecated` is an explicit admin-controlled deprecation mechanism. The ability to deprecate a market is an intended governance action, not an accidental bypass."},{"title":"Pause Guardian Can Pause Critical Functions","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The pause guardian is an intentional emergency-control role documented in storage comments. This is a trust/governance feature, not a bug."}]}
